{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":316,"text":"What I want you all to do right now"},{"time":2838,"text":"is to think of this mammal that I'm going to describe to you."},{"time":7029,"text":"The first thing I'm going to tell you about this mammal"},{"time":9877,"text":"is that it is essential for our ecosystems to function correctly."},{"time":14205,"text":"If we remove this mammal from our ecosystems,"},{"time":17267,"text":"they simply will not work."},{"time":20339,"text":"That's the first thing."},{"time":22029,"text":"The second thing is that due to the unique sensory abilities"},{"time":26706,"text":"of this mammal, if we study this mammal,"},{"time":30860,"text":"we're going to get great insight into our diseases"},{"time":34422,"text":"of the senses, such as blindness and deafness."},{"time":38958,"text":"And the third really intriguing aspect of this mammal"},{"time":43728,"text":"is that I fully believe that the secret of everlasting youth"},{"time":48922,"text":"lies deep within its DNA."},{"time":52977,"text":"So are you all thinking?"},{"time":55285,"text":"So,"},{"time":57779,"text":"magnificent creature, isn't it?"},{"time":60881,"text":"Who here thought of a bat?"},{"time":64233,"text":"Ah, I can see half the audience agrees with me,"},{"time":66864,"text":"and I have a lot of work to do to convince the rest of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70087,"text":"So I have had the good fortune for the past 20 years"},{"time":74345,"text":"to study these fascinating and beautiful mammals."},{"time":78744,"text":"One fifth of all living mammals is a bat,"},{"time":82506,"text":"and they have very unique attributes."},{"time":84918,"text":"Bats as we know them have been around on this planet"},{"time":87946,"text":"for about 64 million years."},{"time":91929,"text":"One of the most unique things that bats do"},{"time":95394,"text":"as a mammal is that they fly."},{"time":98195,"text":"Now flight is an inherently difficult thing."},{"time":101530,"text":"Flight within vertebrates has only evolved three times:"},{"time":105473,"text":"once in the bats, once in the birds,"},{"time":108833,"text":"and once in the pterodactyls."},{"time":110928,"text":"And so with flight, it's very metabolically costly."},{"time":114774,"text":"Bats have learned and evolved how to deal with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118704,"text":"But one other extremely unique thing about bats"},{"time":123090,"text":"is that they are able to use sound"},{"time":125139,"text":"to perceive their environment. They use echolocation."},{"time":129935,"text":"Now, what I mean by echolocation --"},{"time":132599,"text":"they emit a sound from their larynx out through their mouth"},{"time":136104,"text":"or through their nose. This sound wave comes out"},{"time":140000,"text":"and it reflects and echoes back off objects in their environment,"},{"time":144087,"text":"and the bats then hear these echoes"},{"time":146947,"text":"and they turn this information into an acoustic image."},{"time":150465,"text":"And this enables them to orient in complete darkness."},{"time":155093,"text":"Indeed, they do look very strange. We're humans."},{"time":158518,"text":"We're a visual species. When scientists first realized"},{"time":161713,"text":"that bats were actually using sound to be able to fly"},{"time":165654,"text":"and orient and move at night, we didn't believe it."},{"time":168629,"text":"For a hundred years, despite evidence to show"},{"time":171653,"text":"that this is what they were doing, we didn't believe it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174892,"text":"Now, if you look at this bat, it looks a little bit alien."},{"time":178860,"text":"Indeed, the very famous philosopher Thomas Nagel"},{"time":182158,"text":"once said, \"To truly experience an alien life form"},{"time":185663,"text":"on this planet, you should lock yourself inside a room"},{"time":189403,"text":"with a flying, echolocating bat in complete darkness.\""},{"time":193528,"text":"And if you look at the actual physical characteristics"},{"time":196599,"text":"on the face of this beautiful horseshoe bat,"},{"time":199556,"text":"you see a lot of these characteristics are dedicated"},{"time":202350,"text":"to be able to make sound and perceive it."},{"time":205689,"text":"Very big ears, strange nose leaves, but teeny-tiny eyes."},{"time":210253,"text":"So again, if you just look at this bat, you realize"},{"time":214142,"text":"sound is very important for its survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217416,"text":"Most bats look like the previous one."},{"time":221785,"text":"However, there are a group that do not use echolocation."},{"time":225824,"text":"They do not perceive their environment using sound,"},{"time":228823,"text":"and these are the flying foxes."},{"time":230569,"text":"If anybody has ever been lucky enough to be in Australia,"},{"time":233839,"text":"you've seen them coming out of the Botanic Gardens in Sydney,"},{"time":237064,"text":"and if you just look at their face, you can see"},{"time":240249,"text":"they have much, much larger eyes and much smaller ears."},{"time":243787,"text":"So among and within bats is a huge variation"},{"time":247309,"text":"in their ability to use sensory perception."},{"time":250200,"text":"Now this is going to be important for what I'm going"},{"time":252253,"text":"to tell you later during the talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254016,"text":"Now, if the idea of bats in your belfry terrifies you,"},{"time":259095,"text":"and I know some people probably are feeling a little sick"},{"time":261964,"text":"looking at very large images of bats,"},{"time":265168,"text":"that's probably not that surprising,"},{"time":268057,"text":"because here in Western culture,"},{"time":270384,"text":"bats have been demonized."},{"time":272141,"text":"Really, of course the famous book \"Dracula,\""},{"time":274805,"text":"written by a fellow Northside Dubliner Bram Stoker,"},{"time":277888,"text":"probably is mainly responsible for this."},{"time":279945,"text":"However, I also think it's got to do with the fact"},{"time":283025,"text":"that bats come out at night, and we don't"},{"time":285308,"text":"really understand them. We're a little frightened by things"},{"time":287960,"text":"that can perceive the world slightly differently than us."},{"time":291260,"text":"Bats are usually synonymous with some type of evil events."},{"time":294319,"text":"They are the perpetrators in horror movies,"},{"time":297184,"text":"such as this famous \"Nightwing.\""},{"time":298991,"text":"Also, if you think about it, demons"},{"time":301752,"text":"always have bat wings, whereas birds, they typically --"},{"time":305467,"text":"or angels have bird wings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308336,"text":"Now, this is Western society, and what I hope to do tonight"},{"time":313445,"text":"is to convince you of the Chinese traditional culture,"},{"time":318144,"text":"that they perceive bats as"},{"time":321073,"text":"creatures that bring good luck, and indeed, if you walk"},{"time":324657,"text":"into a Chinese home, you may see an image such as this."},{"time":329001,"text":"This is considered the Five Blessings."},{"time":331183,"text":"The Chinese word for \"bat\" sounds like the Chinese word"},{"time":333845,"text":"for \"happiness,\" and they believe that bats"},{"time":336936,"text":"bring wealth, health, longevity, virtue and serenity."},{"time":341297,"text":"And indeed, in this image, you have a picture of longevity"},{"time":344657,"text":"surrounded by five bats."},{"time":346755,"text":"And what I want to do tonight is to talk to you"},{"time":350438,"text":"and to show you that at least three of these blessings"},{"time":354024,"text":"are definitely represented by a bat, and that if we study bats"},{"time":357393,"text":"we will get nearer to getting each of these blessings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361656,"text":"So, wealth -- how can a bat possibly bring us wealth?"},{"time":366707,"text":"Now as I said before, bats are essential for our ecosystems"},{"time":370217,"text":"to function correctly. And why is this?"},{"time":373889,"text":"Bats in the tropics are major pollinators of many plants."},{"time":378003,"text":"They also feed on fruit, and they disperse the seeds"},{"time":380995,"text":"of these fruits. Bats are responsible for pollinating"},{"time":385103,"text":"the tequila plant, and this is a multi-million dollar industry"},{"time":388756,"text":"in Mexico. So indeed, we need them"},{"time":391717,"text":"for our ecosystems to function properly."},{"time":394109,"text":"Without them, it's going to be a problem."},{"time":396844,"text":"But most bats are voracious insect predators."},{"time":402366,"text":"It's been estimated in the U.S., in a tiny colony"},{"time":405242,"text":"of big brown bats, that they will feed"},{"time":407393,"text":"on over a million insects a year,"},{"time":410963,"text":"and in the United States of America, right now"},{"time":413906,"text":"bats are being threatened by a disease known as white-nose syndrome."},{"time":417247,"text":"It's working its way slowly across the U.S. and wiping out"},{"time":420487,"text":"populations of bats, and scientists have estimated"},{"time":424247,"text":"that 1,300 metric tons of insects a year are now"},{"time":429204,"text":"remaining in the ecosystems due to the loss of bats."},{"time":432918,"text":"Bats are also threatened in the U.S."},{"time":435330,"text":"by their attraction to wind farms. Again, right now"},{"time":439169,"text":"bats are looking at a little bit of a problem."},{"time":440893,"text":"They're going to -- They are very threatened"},{"time":443191,"text":"in the United States of America alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446736,"text":"Now how can this help us?"},{"time":448277,"text":"Well, it has been calculated that if we were to remove bats"},{"time":451942,"text":"from the equation, we're going to have to then use"},{"time":454336,"text":"insecticides to remove all those pest insects"},{"time":457277,"text":"that feed on our agricultural crops."},{"time":460352,"text":"And for one year in the U.S. alone, it's estimated"},{"time":464000,"text":"that it's going to cost 22 billion U.S. dollars,"},{"time":466942,"text":"if we remove bats. So indeed, bats then do bring us wealth."},{"time":471465,"text":"They maintain the health of our ecosystems,"},{"time":473921,"text":"and also they save us money."},{"time":476410,"text":"So again, that's the first blessing. Bats are important"},{"time":479297,"text":"for our ecosystems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481953,"text":"And what about the second? What about health?"},{"time":485953,"text":"Inside every cell in your body lies your genome."},{"time":490615,"text":"Your genome is made up of your DNA,"},{"time":493265,"text":"your DNA codes for proteins that enable you to function"},{"time":496457,"text":"and interact and be as you are."},{"time":499377,"text":"Now since the new advancements in modern molecular technologies,"},{"time":503839,"text":"it is now possible for us to sequence our own genome"},{"time":507962,"text":"in a very rapid time and at a very, very reduced cost."},{"time":512091,"text":"Now when we've been doing this, we've realized"},{"time":514631,"text":"that there's variations within our genome."},{"time":518448,"text":"So I want you to look at the person beside you."},{"time":521642,"text":"Just have a quick look. And what we need to realize"},{"time":523721,"text":"is that every 300 base pairs in your DNA, you're a little bit different."},{"time":528365,"text":"And one of the grand challenges right now"},{"time":530630,"text":"in modern molecular medicine is to work out"},{"time":533226,"text":"whether this variation makes you more susceptible to diseases,"},{"time":538068,"text":"or does this variation just make you different?"},{"time":540979,"text":"Again, what does it mean here? What does this variation"},{"time":543385,"text":"actually mean? So if we are to capitalize on all of this"},{"time":547204,"text":"new molecular data and personalized genomic information"},{"time":551098,"text":"that is coming online that we will be able to have"},{"time":553499,"text":"in the next few years, we have to be able to differentiate"},{"time":556571,"text":"between the two. So how do we do this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":559787,"text":"Well, I believe we just look at nature's experiments."},{"time":563115,"text":"So through natural selection, over time,"},{"time":567960,"text":"mutations, variations that disrupt the function of a protein"},{"time":573077,"text":"will not be tolerated over time."},{"time":575698,"text":"Evolution acts as a sieve. It sieves out the bad variation."},{"time":579892,"text":"And so therefore, if you look at the same region"},{"time":582153,"text":"of a genome in many mammals that have been"},{"time":585304,"text":"evolutionarily distant from each other"},{"time":588808,"text":"and are also ecologically divergent, you will get a better"},{"time":592271,"text":"understanding of what the evolutionary prior of that site is,"},{"time":596033,"text":"i.e., if it is important for the mammal to function,"},{"time":599912,"text":"for its survival, it will be the same"},{"time":602232,"text":"in all of those different lineages, species, taxa."},{"time":606983,"text":"So therefore, if we were to do this,"},{"time":610260,"text":"what we'd need to do is sequence that region"},{"time":611729,"text":"in all these different mammals and ascertain if it's the same"},{"time":614844,"text":"or if it's different. So if it is the same,"},{"time":618851,"text":"this indicates that that site is important for a function,"},{"time":621960,"text":"so a disease mutation should fall within that site."},{"time":625823,"text":"So in this case here, if all the mammals that we look at"},{"time":629560,"text":"have a yellow-type genome at that site,"},{"time":632824,"text":"it probably suggests that purple is bad."},{"time":635486,"text":"This could be even more powerful if you look at mammals"},{"time":638960,"text":"that are doing things slightly differently."},{"time":641632,"text":"So say, for example, the region of the genome"},{"time":643710,"text":"that I was looking at was a region that's important for vision."},{"time":647239,"text":"If we look at that region in mammals that don't see so well,"},{"time":650913,"text":"such as bats, and we find that bats that don't see so well"},{"time":654747,"text":"have the purple type, we know that this is probably"},{"time":657519,"text":"what's causing this disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660894,"text":"So in my lab, we've been using bats to look at two different"},{"time":665087,"text":"types of diseases of the senses."},{"time":668435,"text":"We're looking at blindness. Now why would you do this?"},{"time":671243,"text":"Three hundred and fourteen million people are visually impaired, and"},{"time":676189,"text":"45 million of these are blind. So blindness is a big problem,"},{"time":679780,"text":"and a lot of these blind disorders come from inherited diseases,"},{"time":683995,"text":"so we want to try and better understand"},{"time":686166,"text":"which mutations in the gene cause the disease."},{"time":689771,"text":"Also we look at deafness. One in every 1,000"},{"time":693679,"text":"newborn babies are deaf, and when we reach 80,"},{"time":697195,"text":"over half of us will also have a hearing problem."},{"time":700253,"text":"Again, there's many underlying genetic causes for this."},{"time":704530,"text":"So what we've been doing in my lab"},{"time":707177,"text":"is looking at these unique sensory specialists, the bats,"},{"time":710291,"text":"and we have looked at genes that cause blindness"},{"time":712839,"text":"when there's a defect in them,"},{"time":714188,"text":"genes that cause deafness when there's a defect in them,"},{"time":716731,"text":"and now we can predict which sites are most likely to cause disease."},{"time":721721,"text":"So bats are also important for our health,"},{"time":724602,"text":"to enable us to better understand how our genome functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729492,"text":"So this is where we are right now,"},{"time":731911,"text":"but what about the future?"},{"time":733811,"text":"What about longevity?"},{"time":735467,"text":"This is where we're going to go, and as I said before,"},{"time":739208,"text":"I really believe that the secret of everlasting youth"},{"time":742287,"text":"lies within the bat genome."},{"time":743996,"text":"So why should we be interested in aging at all?"},{"time":748112,"text":"Well, really, this is a picture drawn from the 1500s"},{"time":750600,"text":"of the Fountain of Youth. Aging is considered"},{"time":754416,"text":"one of the most familiar, yet the least well-understood,"},{"time":758051,"text":"aspects of all of biology, and really,"},{"time":761013,"text":"since the dawn of civilization, mankind has sought to avoid it."},{"time":765389,"text":"But we are going to have to understand it a bit better."},{"time":768434,"text":"In Europe alone, by 2050, there is going to be"},{"time":772063,"text":"a 70 percent increase of individuals over 65,"},{"time":775878,"text":"and 170 percent increase in individuals over 80."},{"time":779615,"text":"As we age, we deteriorate, and this deterioration"},{"time":782456,"text":"causes problems for our society, so we have to address it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787218,"text":"So how could the secret of everlasting youth actually lie"},{"time":791732,"text":"within the bat genome? Does anybody want to hazard"},{"time":794413,"text":"a guess over how long this bat could live for?"},{"time":798371,"text":"Who -- put up your hands -- who says two years?"},{"time":801396,"text":"Nobody? One? How about 10 years?"},{"time":805292,"text":"Some? How about 30?"},{"time":809144,"text":"How about 40? Okay, it's a whole varied response."},{"time":813019,"text":"This bat is myotis brandtii. It's the longest-living bat."},{"time":816670,"text":"It lived for up to 42 years,"},{"time":818858,"text":"and this bat's still alive in the wild today."},{"time":821193,"text":"But what would be so amazing about this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":823775,"text":"Well, typically, in mammals there is a relationship"},{"time":828857,"text":"between body size, metabolic rate,"},{"time":831357,"text":"and how long you can live for, and you can predict"},{"time":833493,"text":"how long a mammal can live for given its body size."},{"time":836720,"text":"So typically, small mammals live fast, die young."},{"time":840415,"text":"Think of a mouse. But bats are very different."},{"time":843154,"text":"As you can see here on this graph, in blue,"},{"time":845970,"text":"these are all other mammals, but bats"},{"time":848536,"text":"can live up to nine times longer than expected"},{"time":850704,"text":"despite having a really, really high metabolic rate,"},{"time":853846,"text":"and the question is, how can they do that?"},{"time":856481,"text":"There are 19 species of mammal that live longer"},{"time":860022,"text":"than expected, given their body size, than man,"},{"time":862798,"text":"and 18 of those are bats."},{"time":865646,"text":"So therefore, they must have something within their DNA"},{"time":870582,"text":"that ables them to deal with the metabolic stresses,"},{"time":873427,"text":"particularly of flight. They expend three times more energy"},{"time":877333,"text":"than a mammal of the same size,"},{"time":878873,"text":"but don't seem to suffer the consequences or the effects."},{"time":882485,"text":"So right now, in my lab, we're combining"},{"time":885830,"text":"state-of-the-art bat field biology, going out and catching"},{"time":889741,"text":"the long-lived bats, with the most up-to-date,"},{"time":892550,"text":"modern molecular technology to understand better"},{"time":896021,"text":"what it is that they do to stop aging as we do."},{"time":900549,"text":"And hopefully in the next five years, I'll be giving you a TEDTalk on that."},{"time":903709,"text":"Aging is a big problem for humanity,"},{"time":907308,"text":"and I believe that by studying bats, we can uncover"},{"time":910244,"text":"the molecular mechanisms that enable mammals"},{"time":913116,"text":"to achieve extraordinary longevity. If we find out"},{"time":916325,"text":"what they're doing, perhaps through gene therapy,"},{"time":919557,"text":"we can enable us to do the same thing."},{"time":922116,"text":"Potentially, this means that we could halt aging or maybe even reverse it."},{"time":927392,"text":"Just imagine what that would be like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931283,"text":"So really, I don't think we should be thinking of them"},{"time":934168,"text":"as flying demons of the night, but more as our superheroes."},{"time":939222,"text":"And the reality is that bats can bring us so much benefit"},{"time":943068,"text":"if we just look in the right place. They're good for our ecosystem,"},{"time":945620,"text":"they allow us to understand how our genome functions,"},{"time":948526,"text":"and they potentially hold the secret to everlasting youth."},{"time":951755,"text":"So tonight, when you walk out of here and you look up"},{"time":954370,"text":"in the night skies, and you see this beautiful flying mammal,"},{"time":957869,"text":"I want you to smile. Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}